unsub();", " typescript", " nav_events.ts") Enhanced Links Navigation Optimizer Impact Each optimization can be configured independently and measured with browser DevTools (TTI, layout shift, and next-click latency). 1) Speculative Prefetching Viewport + hover intent prefetch reduces click-to-paint latency on docs navigation. 2) Optimized Click Delegation Container-scoped listener with composedPath avoids expensive global target walks. 3) Incremental DOM Patching Only changed nodes/attrs are patched, preserving listeners and minimizing churn. 4) URL Parsing Cache LRU-style URL parsing cache removes repeated `new URL(...)` overhead on dense pages. 5) Idle Batch Head Updates Moves non-critical head reconciliation to idle periods. 6) Lazy Runtime Init Critical handlers attach immediately; bindings are deferred to idle. 7) Service Worker HTML Cache Network-first with cache fallback keeps docs navigable during flaky connectivity. 8) View Transitions API Smooth route transitions when supported, classic updates otherwise. Instant Navigation GoSPA provides immediate feedback by updating the URL and active link states before the network request completes. This makes your app feel as fast as a local application. Loading State Attribute During background loads, the main container receives data-gospa-loading=" true" . Use it to style loading indicators. Route Params ;
